OL,3,CThe price of an underpoured pint:
OL,4,CShort measures cost drinkers #115 a
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FThat means around 70% of drinks were
OL,8,Fless than the prescribed quantity
OL,9,Frequired by the Weights and Measures
OL,10,FOrder for pints, half pints, and 175ml
OL,11,Fglasses of wine.
OL,13,FSome 86% of all beer ordered was short
OL,14,Fmeasured, as was 43% of wine.
OL,16,FAnd that shortfall adds up. CTSI Chief
OL,17,FExecutive, John Herriman, said there
OL,18,Fwas a "potential detriment to the
OL,19,Faverage consumer of around #115 every
OL,20,Fyear."
