OL,4,CShort measures cost drinkers #115 a
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FThe average deficit for short-measured
OL,8,Fbeer was 4%, while for wine it was 5%.
OL,10,FPunters might find this news hard to
OL,11,Fswallow, as the findings come at a
OL,12,Ftime when the price of
OL,14,FThe average price of a bottle of red
OL,15,Fwine has increased by 8% in the last
OL,16,Fyear, while the average cost of a pint
OL,17,Fof lager is up 5.6%, according to the
OL,18,FOffice for National Statistics.
